From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nunchi Operators <nunchi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 18:14:46 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] discord: drop only self-messages so allowlisted peer bots
 are heard

Replace the unconditional bot-drop in the messageCreate handler with a
self-only guard. The unconditional drop ran before gate(), so a peer bot
explicitly allowlisted by the operator was never heard (upstream issues
anthropics/claude-plugins-official#1153, #1559). With this patch bot
authors flow into gate() like any other sender and must satisfy
dmPolicy/allowFrom (DMs) or the per-channel group policy before
delivery. The self-guard preserves the original echo-loop prevention.
---
 server.ts | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/server.ts b/server.ts
index 0b346f5..9162be1 100644
--- a/server.ts
+++ b/server.ts
@@ -905,7 +905,13 @@ client.on('interactionCreate', async (interaction: Interaction) => {
 })
 
 client.on('messageCreate', msg => {
-  if (msg.author.bot) return
+  // Drop only our own messages (echo-loop guard). Peer bots are NOT dropped
+  // here: gate()/allowFrom in access.json remains the authorization layer,
+  // and a bot sender must satisfy dmPolicy/allowFrom or the per-channel
+  // group policy exactly like a human before its messages are delivered.
+  // Upstream: anthropics/claude-plugins-official issues #1153 and #1559;
+  // community reference chenjr0719 fix/allow-bot-messages (e0474df).
+  if (msg.author.id === client.user?.id) return
   handleInbound(msg).catch(e => process.stderr.write(`discord: handleInbound failed: ${e}\n`))
 })
 
